  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the tava griddle over medium-low heat.",
    "Butter 4 slices of white bread, leaving a 1/2-inch border around each slice.",
    "Fold each slice of bread in half lengthwise.",
    "In a small bowl, beat the eggs and mix in the milk, a pinch of salt, and a few grinds of black pepper.",
    "Pour the egg mixture over the folded bread slices.",
    "Cook for 2-3 minutes, until the egg is almost set.",
    "Sprinkle the grated Parmesan cheese over the bread.",
    "Fold the bread in half again and cook for an additional 1-2 minutes, until the cheese is melted and the bread is golden brown.",
    "Serve the toast hot, garnished with chopped fresh chives.",
    "Repeat the process with the remaining bread slices."
  ],
